File: The deployment of the team comes after 204 learners and hostel assistants tested positive for COVID-19. KWABHACA - The Eastern Cape Department of Health has deployed a team of doctors and tracers to the Makaula Senior Secondary School in KwaBhaca. The deployment comes after 204 learners and hostel assistants tested positive for COVID-19. READ: Calls for schools to be shut down The department is now trying to prevent the further spread of the virus. It is also looking into possibly converting the hostel into an isolation facility as another measure of preventing the further spread of the coronavirus. READ: Sadtu wants Eastern Cape schools to shut down A team of clinicians have already been sent to the school. They will ascertain if the hostel meets minimum standards for quarantine and isolation facilities. . READ: Concerns mount over Eastern Cape COVID-19 infections Those that have tested positive are in isolation within the Alfred Nzo District Municipal area. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.